cs.NI, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a load balancing packet switch and discusses its performance under different traffic scenarios. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper describes the architecture of the proposed switch and its configuration scheme. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses load balancing and routing of traffic in a network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a switch with deterministic scheduling and analyzes its performance. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the throughput analysis of the proposed switch.
